# DATA CONTRACT & OUTPUT SCHEMAS

Whenever processing text, the LLM backend router must explicitly adhere to these structured output patterns:

### Skill 1: generate_structured_notes
Expected output data signature:
{
  "core_concepts": [
    { "timestamp": "00:00", "concept_title": "string", "summary_bullets": ["string"] }
  ],
  "problem_solving_rationale": { "problem_statement": "string", "why_this_approach": "string" },
  "key_takeaways": ["string"]
}

### Skill 2: extract_math_and_logic
Expected output data signature:
{
  "has_math": true,
  "math_blocks": [{ "description": "string", "latex_expression": "string" }],
  "has_logic": true,
  "logic_blocks": [{ "block_title": "string", "pseudocode": "string" }]
}

### Skill 3: simulate_dry_run_trace
Expected output data signature:
{
  "input_received": "string",
  "variable_tracking_headers": ["Step", "Variable1", "Variable2"],
  "trace_steps": [
    ["1", "value1", "value2"]
  ],
  "final_state_summary": "string"
}